Key Match Events: Romain Saiss scored the first goal for Morocco at the 30th minute
Tanzania's Novatus Miroshi was sent off with a red card with 20 minutes left to play
Azzedine Ounahi doubled Morocco's lead at the 77th minute
Youssef En-Nesyri scored the third goal for Morocco at the 80th minute
Pre-Game Insights: Morocco is the pre-tournament favorite for the 2023 Africa Cup of Nations
Tanzania is ranked 121 by FIFA, while Morocco is ranked 13
Post-Match Reflections: Walid Regragui, Morocco's coach, expressed caution about the hype surrounding the team's performance
Miscellaneous Highlights: This is Morocco's first match in the 2023 Africa Cup of Nations
Tanzania has never won a match in the Africa Cup of Nations
Others: Morocco is one of the 12 teams that have won the Africa Cup of Nations before but it has been a long time since their last win in 1976
Tanzania has participated in the Africa Cup of Nations three times, in 1980 and 2019, and has never won a match
